1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 22 MRSA ยง1812-M is enacted to read:
3 ยง1812-M. Urgent care facility
4 1. Definition. "Urgent care facility" means a health care facility that is not otherwise
5 licensed with a primary purpose of providing medical evaluation and care on a walk-in
6 basis for non-life-threatening injuries and illnesses. As used in this chapter, "urgent care
7 facility" does not include:
8 A. A facility that is licensed as part of a hospital;
9 B. A facility that provides services or accommodations for patients who stay overnight;
10 or
11 C. The private office of a physician or dentist in individual or group practice.
12 2. Standards. The department shall establish standards for the licensure of urgent
13 care facilities effective July 1, 2026. The standards must include a licensure fee of not less
14 than $50 and not more than $500 and address staffing, quality of care, advertising and
15 promotion, inspections and complaint investigations and accreditation.
16 SUMMARY
1177 This bill provides a definition for "urgent care facility," which excludes a facility that
1188 is licensed as part of a hospital, provides services or accommodations for patients who stay
1199 overnight or is the location of the private office of a physician or dentist. The bill also
2200 requires the Department of Health and Human Services to establish licensing standards for
2211 urgent care facilities.
